text:
Economic bee hoon is delicious, fried noodle is not too shabby either.
Eggs are runny, just the way I like them. Do try the fried chicken wings also.
Decent fried bee Hoon in the morning. Dry springy type

This morning I ordered rice noodles + fried chicken wings + poached eggs + vegetarian goose. It tastes great, and the fried rice noodles and fried noodles are both hot. The portion of rice noodles given by auntie is really large, but it's just a bit greasy. In the afternoon, it is not open at night.
